When #bitcoin is sent to someone it doesn't suddenly arrive on their phone/USB/wallet. 

A transaction just updates the distributed ledger to say that this wallet owns this amount of #bitcoin. 

Millions of computers are competing to keep track of this ledger and your BTC via PoW

Many cryptocurrencies love talking about "speed", but TRUST > "Speed"
